id: pm-ae1u
title: "item-format-migration: add format-version field to front-matter for future migration gating"
description: "There is no explicit format/schema version field in TOON front-matter. When a breaking front-matter change ships, there is no per-item version gate to distinguish items that need migration from items that are already migrated. The migrateItemFilesToFormat function performs an expensive full-corpus pass on every mutation; a version stamp would let it skip up-to-date items much faster."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:storage",migration,tech-debt
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:03:32.173Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:16:06.227Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Propose and evaluate adding `pm_format_version: 1` to the TOON front-matter schema\n- If approved: `item-format-migration.ts` stamps the version on write and gates migration on version < current\n- `pm validate` checks format version; `pm health` warns on outdated items\n- ADR candidate: whether to add a version field or keep relying on structural detection"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: medium
body: "## Context\n\n`src/core/store/item-format-migration.ts` handles migrations but relies on structural content inspection (does the file look like old format?) rather than an explicit version. The performance fix in session 2026-05-31 (PR#87) added a skip for already-migrated items based on format detection, but a true version field would be more robust and enable staged multi-version migrations.\n\nExisting ADR: TOON canonical storage is in place. A `pm_format_version` front-matter field would be a very lightweight addition.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Propose and evaluate adding `pm_format_version: 1` to the TOON front-matter schema\n- [ ] If approved: `item-format-migration.ts` stamps the version on write and gates migration on version < current\n- [ ] `pm validate` checks format version; `pm health` warns on outdated items\n- [ ] ADR candidate: whether to add a version field or keep relying on structural detection\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/core/store/item-format-migration.ts` — no version field; uses structural detection\n- PR#87 memory note: 'pre-mutation migrateItemFilesToFormat re-parsed the WHOLE corpus every mutation (now skips already-migrated items)' — the skip is heuristic, not version-based"
